==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stercoranist
<hw>Ster"co*ra*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>stercoranista</ets>, fr. L. <ets>stercus</ets>, <ets>-oris</ets>,
dung.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A nickname formerly given to
those who held, or were alleged to hold, that the consecrated elements
in the eucharist undergo the process of digestion in the body of the
recipient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stercorarian</ent>⟦br⟧
